-- German Stocks Rise as BMW, Fresenius Advance; Metro Declines in Frankfurt
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-10-29T13:52:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/german-stocks-rise-as-bmw-fresenius-advance-metro-declines-in-frankfurt.html
German stocks advanced, as gains in
shares of Fresenius SE and Bayerische Motoren Werke AG
overshadwoed a selloff in Metro AG.  The benchmark DAX Index rose 0.4 percent to 6,618.91 at
3:49 p.m. in Frankfurt, extending its advance this month to 6.2
percent, the best performance since March.  BMW rallied 3 percent as Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
recommended buying the shares. Fresenius gained 3.9 percent as
Deutsche Bank AG lifted its price forecast for the stock. Metro,
Germany’s biggest retailer, slipped 2 percent as  HSBC Holdings
Plc cut its recommendation on the shares to “neutral” from
“overweight.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  